    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-02-04T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-02-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <head>156. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d156fn0"
                        >Source: Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 64 D 560, <gloss
                            target="#t_CF1">CF</gloss> 1201. Top Secret; Limit Distribution. Drafted
                        by <persName corresp="#p_HMJ1">Hillenbrand</persName>. The meeting was held
                        at the Embassy Residence.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <gloss target="#t_SVEMC1">SVE/MC</gloss>–9</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>London</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1959-02-04T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 4, 1959, 3:00 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Berlin</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>The Secretary</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NGL1">General Norstad</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WJH1">Whitney</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BW1">Barbour</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GJNJ1">Greene</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_TRL1">Thurston</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HMJ1">Hillenbrand</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The discussion of this subject started with a reference to the American convoy
                    which was being held at the Marienborn checkpoint.<note n="1" xml:id="d156fn1"
                        >See <ref target="#d152">Document 152</ref>.</note>
                    <pb facs="0342" n="317" xml:id="pg_317"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NGL1">General Norstad</persName> remarked that there was
                    some reason for believing that a local Soviet interpretation of the inspection
                    procedure was involved. The Secretary said that another interpretation might be
                    that the Soviets wanted to stiffen up their position to create a precedent
                    before turning over to the <gloss target="#t_GDR1">GDR</gloss>. <persName
                        corresp="#p_NGL1">General Norstad</persName> said this would be more likely
                    if it had occurred at the Berlin end of the autobahn. [<hi rend="italic">8 lines
                        of source text not declassified</hi>]</p>
            </div>
